	<text>
		<body xml:lang="en">
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002064_0001"/><!--pb/@n='76r'-->
<lb/><p><placeName>Hamilton</placeName> 10<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">th</hi></hi> Sept<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">r</hi></hi>
<lb/>1864 </p>
<lb/><p>My Dear Sir 
<lb/>I return my very 
<lb/>hearty thanks for your 
<lb/>kind invitation to join 
<lb/>the "Gaiter Club." <choice><reg>B</reg><orig>b</orig></choice>ut 
<lb/>I had engaged to go to the 
<lb/>meeting of the British 
<lb/><choice><reg>A</reg><orig>a</orig></choice>ssociation at Bath, 
<lb/>and <add place="above">also</add> arranged to leave 
<lb/>this for the south 
<lb/>on <choice><reg>M</reg><orig>m</orig></choice>onday where I 
<lb/>shall be for two or 
<lb/>three months. I fear 
<lb/>I am thus precluded 
<lb/>from the pleasure of 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002064_0002"/><!--pb/@n='76v'-->
<lb/>attending a meeting 
<lb/>of the members. </p>
<lb/><p>The object of the club 
<lb/>does not appear very 
<lb/>prominently on the face 
<lb/>of the constitution 
<w>con-<lb break="no"/>tained</w> in the pamphlet 
<lb/>for which I have to 
<lb/>thank you - unless 
<lb/>flumina amo silvasque 
<lb/>denotes rollicking 
<lb/>among woods &amp; 
<lb/>waters to which I 
<lb/>have had a strong 
<lb/>propensity ever 
<lb/>since I first opened 
<lb/>my eyes<reg>.</reg></p>

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002064_0003"/><!--pb/@n='77r'-->
<lb/><p>Although I am prevented 
<lb/>from waiting upon 
<lb/>you I very highly 
<lb/>appreciate the 
<lb/>kindly feeling with 
<lb/>which you remembered 
<lb/>my name and am 
<lb/>yours very cordially </p>
<lb/><p><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>
<lb/><p><persName>John Burns Esq.</persName></p>
			
